{"title_page": "Lu\u00eds Carlos (footballer, born 1972)", "text_new": "{{short description|Portuguese footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name = Lu\u00eds Carlos\n|image = \n|fullname = Lu\u00eds Carlos da Silva Marques\n|birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1972|8|21|df=y}}\n|birth_place = [[Castro Daire]], Portugal\n|height = 1.77 m\n|position = [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]]\n|youthyears1 = 1985\u20131991 | youthclubs1 = [[Clube Oriental de Lisboa|Oriental]]\n|years1 = 1991\u20131996 | clubs1 = [[Clube Oriental de Lisboa|Oriental]] | caps1 = | goals1 =\n|years2 = 1996\u20131997 | clubs2 = [[C.D. Nacional|Nacional]] | caps2 = | goals2 =\n|years3 = 1997 | clubs3 = [[S.C. Salgueiros|Salgueiros]] | caps3 = 10 | goals3 = 1\n|years4 = 1998\u20132000 | clubs4 = [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] | caps4 = 45 | goals4 = 1\n|years5 = 2000\u20132001 | clubs5 = [[Estrela da Amadora|Estrela Amadora]] | caps5 = 12 | goals5 = 0\n|years6 = 2001\u20132002 | clubs6 = [[Atl\u00e9tico Clube de Portugal|Atl\u00e9tico]] | caps6 = 35 | goals6 = 4\n|years7 = 2002\u20132004 | clubs7 = [[G.D. Estoril Praia|Estoril]] | caps7 = 38 | goals7 = 1\n|years8 = 2004\u20132007 | clubs8 = Beira-Mar Monte Gordo | caps8 = | goals8 =\n|totalcaps = 140 | totalgoals = 7\n|nationalyears1 = 1998 | nationalteam1 = [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] | nationalcaps1= 1 | nationalgoals1 = 0\n}}\n'''Lu\u00eds Carlos da Silva Marques''' (born 21 August 1972), known as '''Lu\u00eds Carlos''', is a former Portuguese [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Midfielder#Winger|left winger]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[Castro Daire]], [[Viseu District]], Lu\u00eds Carlos joined [[Clube Oriental de Lisboa]]'s youth system in 1985, going on to compete with the club as a senior in the lower leagues. In 1996, he signed with [[C.D. Nacional]], helping his team [[1996\u201397 Segunda Divis\u00e3o B|achieve promotion]] from the [[Portuguese Second Division|third division]].\n\nLu\u00eds Carlos moved straight to the [[Primeira Liga]] in the 1997 summer, when he joined [[S.C. Salgueiros]]. In the following [[transfer window]], after solid performances, he moved to [[S.L. Benfica]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Salgueiros quer Lu\u00eds Carlos ou Prof\u00edrio |trans-title=Salgueiros wants Luis Carlos or Porfirio |url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/benfica/detalhe/salgueiros-quer-luis-carlos-ou-profirio.html |accessdate=21 June 2018 |work=Record |date=14 December 1999 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> He made his debut on 3 January 1998 against [[FC Porto]], and was a starter for the [[Graeme Souness]]-led side in [[1997\u201398 S.L. Benfica season|his first season]].<ref>{{cite book | last=Tovar |first=Rui Miguel | title=Almanaque do Benfica| publisher=Lua de Papel |location=Portugal| year=2012| isbn=978-989-23-2087-8 |page=556}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | last=Tovar |first=Rui Miguel | title=Almanaque do Benfica| publisher=Lua de Papel |location=Portugal| year=2012| isbn=978-989-23-2087-8 |page=562}}</ref>\n\nSubsequently, Lu\u00eds Carlos was only a fringe player for Benfica, first losing his place to [[Hugo Leal]] then being completely sidelined by [[Jupp Heynckes]] in the [[1999\u20132000 S.L. Benfica season|1999\u20132000 campaign]].<ref>{{cite book | last=Tovar |first=Rui Miguel | title=Almanaque do Benfica| publisher=Lua de Papel |location=Portugal| year=2012| isbn=978-989-23-2087-8 |page=563}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | last=Tovar |first=Rui Miguel | title=Almanaque do Benfica| publisher=Lua de Papel |location=Portugal| year=2012| isbn=978-989-23-2087-8 |page=577}}</ref> After being subjected to disciplinary procedures due to comments he made regarding the latter's releasing of [[Jo\u00e3o Vieira Pinto]], referring to him as \"not much of a man\",<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.xl.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/benfica/detalhe/benfica-instaura-processo-disciplinar-a-luis-carlos.html|title=Benfica instaura processo disciplinar a Lu\u00eds Carlos|trans-title=Lu\u00eds Carlos subjected to disciplinary proceedings at Benfica|newspaper=[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]|language=Portuguese|date=10 June 2000|accessdate=6 September 2015}}</ref> Benfica sent him on a permanent deal to [[C.F. Estrela da Amadora]] together with [[Jorge Cadete]], as [[Miguel Monteiro|Miguel]] moved in the opposite direction.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.xl.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/benfica/detalhe/jorge-cadete-confirmado-no-estrela-da-amadora.html|title=Jorge Cadete confirmado no Estrela da Amadora|trans-title=Cadete confirmed in Estrela da Amadora|newspaper=Record|language=Portuguese|date=23 June 2000|accessdate=6 September 2015}}</ref>\n\nAfter suffering relegation from the top flight at the end of [[2000\u201301 Primeira Liga|the season]], Lu\u00eds Carlos returned to the third level, first with [[Atl\u00e9tico Clube de Portugal]] then [[G.D. Estoril-Praia]], helping the latter club promote to the second tier in [[2002\u201303 Segunda Divis\u00e3o B|2003]]. He retired in 2007 at the age of 35, after three years in amateur football with Grupo Desportivo Beira-Mar.\n\n==International career==\nDuring his tenure with Benfica, Lu\u00eds Carlos earned one [[Cap (sport)|cap]] for [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]], playing the second half of a 2\u20131 [[Exhibition game|friendly]] win with [[Mozambique national football team|Mozambique]] in [[Ponta Delgada]] on 19 August 1998.<ref>{{cite web |title=Lu\u00eds Carlos da Silva Marques |url=https://eu-football.info/_player.php?id=24442 |website=eu-football.info |accessdate=21 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{ForaDeJogo}}\n*{{NFT player}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Luis Carlos}}\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Portuguese footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football wingers]]\n[[Category:Primeira Liga players]]\n[[Category:LigaPro players]]\n[[Category:Portuguese Second Division players]]\n[[Category:Clube Oriental de Lisboa players]]\n[[Category:C.D. Nacional players]]\n[[Category:S.C. Salgueiros players]]\n[[Category:S.L. Benfica footballers]]\n[[Category:C.F. Estrela da Amadora players]]\n[[Category:Atl\u00e9tico Clube de Portugal players]]\n[[Category:G.D. Estoril Praia players]]\n[[Category:Portugal international footballers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Portuguese footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2010}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name = Lu\u00eds Carlos\n|image = \n|fullname = Lu\u00eds Carlos da Silva Marques\n|birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1972|8|21|df=y}}\n|birth_place = [[Castro Daire]], Portugal\n|height = 1.77 m\n|position = [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]]\n|youthyears1 = 1985\u20131991 | youthclubs1 = [[Clube Oriental de Lisboa|Oriental]]\n|years1 = 1991\u20131996 | clubs1 = [[Clube Oriental de Lisboa|Oriental]] | caps1 = | goals1 =\n|years2 = 1996\u20131997 | clubs2 = [[C.D. Nacional|Nacional]] | caps2 = | goals2 =\n|years3 = 1997 | clubs3 = [[S.C. Salgueiros|Salgueiros]] | caps3 = 10 | goals3 = 1\n|years4 = 1998\u20132000 | clubs4 = [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] | caps4 = 45 | goals4 = 1\n|years5 = 2000\u20132001 | clubs5 = [[Estrela da Amadora|Estrela Amadora]] | caps5 = 12 | goals5 = 0\n|years6 = 2001\u20132002 | clubs6 = [[Atl\u00e9tico Clube de Portugal|Atl\u00e9tico]] | caps6 = 35 | goals6 = 4\n|years7 = 2002\u20132004 | clubs7 = [[G.D. Estoril Praia|Estoril]] | caps7 = 38 | goals7 = 1\n|years8 = 2004\u20132007 | clubs8 = Beira-Mar Monte Gordo | caps8 = | goals8 =\n|totalcaps = 140 | totalgoals = 7\n|nationalyears1 = 1998 | nationalteam1 = [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] | nationalcaps1= 1 | nationalgoals1 = 0\n}}\n'''Lu\u00eds Carlos da Silva Marques''' (born 21 August 1972), known as '''Lu\u00eds Carlos''', is a former Portuguese [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Midfielder#Winger|left winger]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn